Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Plea/sentencing hearing on December 7, 2022 at 09:30 am.

1:35 PM; Case called for Hearing.  Defendant Alfonso D Flores in court.  Attorney Jeffrey W. Jensen Jr. in court for Alfonso D Flores.  Prosecuting attorney Andrew Nesheim in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Atty. Jensen provides an update; he is asking the matter be set for plea and sentencing in 45 days.  Court adjourns for plea and sentencing.
Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for December 7, 2022 at 09:30 am.

11:53 AM; Case called for Bail/bond hearing.  Prosecuting attorney Alyssa M. Schaller in court for the State of Wisconsin.   Defendant Alfonso D Flores not in court.  Attorney Steven Hughes, for attorney Jeffrey W. Jensen Jr., in court for Alfonso D Flores.  Court notes the matter was set to address WCS non-compliance report filed on 9/16/2022 but since then WCS has filed a letter advising the defendant is now compliant.  Court also notes the clerk was just informed that the defendant has contacted the clerk's office and is having car trouble and is not able to appear.  Court confirms with counsel they have received the WCS compliance letter.  Based on the defendant now being compliant with WCS the court will not issue a capias and will maintain the previously scheduled further proceedings on 10/19/2022 at 1:30 p.m.  Court will have the clerk's office remind the defendant he must comply with WCS and to appear for his next court date.
Wisconsin Community Service compliance letter received and filed.
Wisconsin Community Service compliance letter received and filed.
Bail/bond hearing on September 26, 2022 at 11:00 am.

10:08 AM; Case called for Bail/bond hearing.  Attorney Randy P. Sitzberger in court for State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Alfonso D Flores in court.  Attorney Jeremy Perri, for attorney Jeffrey W. Jensen Jr., in court for Alfonso D Flores. Court notes the matter is before the Court with respect to WCS non-compliance.  Atty. Perri presents statements with respect to the non-compliance.  Atty. Sitzberger confirms there is an updated letter from WCS advising the defendant has set up an appointment for today after this hearing.  Atty. Sitzberger presents statements; based on the non-compliance he is asking bail be increased.  Atty. Perri responds and is asking the court to take no action with respect to bail at this time.  Defendant presents statements.  For reasons placed on the record the Court will authorize but stay the issuance of a capias to allow the defendant to report to WCS after court today.  If the defendant fails to report to WCS after court or there is a positive test, if tested, then the capias will issue.  WCS to file a letter with the court immediately following the defendant's appointment to provide an update.  Court will also set the matter for a continued bail/bond hearing in about 10 days, but will also maintain the previously set hearing on 10/19/2022 at 1:30 PM.
Bail/bond hearing scheduled for September 26, 2022 at 11:00 am.
